Friends and family members have been left in a state of shock after a 300-level medical student of the Niger Delta University, NDU, allegedly killed himself by plunging into Amassoma River in Bayelsa State. It was gathered that Uzakah Timi Ebiweni, took the decision to end it all, after failing his MBBS exams. Out of the 169 students in his class, 50 failed, according to reports. Timi allegedly started giving hints via his WhatsApp stories by initially posting a candle light and then changing it to the picture of a candle with its light blown off.